## Spec-Driven Development (spec-kit)
When a project contains `.specify/`, it is source-of-truth: `/speckit.constitution → /speckit.specify → /speckit.clarify → /speckit.plan → /speckit.tasks → /speckit.analyze → /speckit.implement`. No feature code without a spec.

Pairs with superpowers: `brainstorming` → `/speckit.specify` → `test-driven-development` → `/speckit.implement`.

## Memory Protocol (LLM-Wiki second brain)
- `MEMORY.md` is the always-loaded index; `memory/hot.md` is the top-of-session warm cache. Both are **generated** — never hand-edit them.
- `memory/{user,feedback,project,reference}/` hold one fact per file (YAML frontmatter `name`/`description`/`metadata.type`, `[[wikilinks]]`); load on demand by topic.
- After adding/editing a memory file, regenerate via the brain toolkit when present (`tools/brain`: `npm run index` + `npm run hot`) and run `npm run lint` (must be 0 errors). Run-logs go to `logs/`, JSONL telemetry to `telemetry/` — never `memory/`.
- One learning per file, no duplicates; verify a recalled fact against current state before acting.

